11 March 2020 The Inter-Ministerial Task Team (IMTT) on the North West intervention under the convenorship of the Minister of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs (CoGTA), Dr Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma, will conduct stakeholder engagements in the province to assess progress on the section (100) (1)Â  intervention in the province since the establishment of the IMTT. The IMTT will engage with the Premier and Provincial Executive as well as with the Speaker and the Provincial Legislature. Members of the media are invited to a photo opportunity and remarks by the Chairperson Dr Nkosazana Dlamini- Zuma as follows: Date: Friday, 13 March 2020 Time: 13h00 (arrival and registration) 14h00 (Photo opportunity) Venue: Council Chambers, Rustenburg Civic Centre Members of the media interested in covering the session are requested to submit their details to Ishmael Selemale at Ishmael@gcis.gov.za or Kagisho Meremetsi at Kagisho@gcis.gov.za before 14h00 on Thursday, 12 March 2020. Enquiries:  Lungi Mtshali Spokesperson for Minister Dlamini Zuma  Cell: 082 088 5060 Phumla Williams  GCIS Acting Director-General  Cell: 083 5010 139